 <h2 id="01">BackupFilePath</h2>

 <p>Backup <i>FilePath</i> to a SQLite database file and access later.</p>

 <p>It could be regarded as a simple versioning system as it is similar, though a backup system was chosen to imply that is not to replace a proper versioning system. It is probably something in between as it is not to replace a proper dedicated backup system either. As it is full content backup, it could also be used to store different variations of a file.</p>

 <p>A versioning system is incremental differencing, while this is full content backup. It can be used within a directory based version system like Git without conflict. It can do this as it is only for the target file. It is suitable for temporary backups or can be long term use like a versioning system. The later is inefficient based on the size increase of the database and might be better instead with a proper versioning system.</p>

 <p>The database name will be like <code>filename.ext.backups</code> if the target file is named <code>filename.ext</code>.</p>

 <p>Modes:</p>

 <ul>
  <li>Commit filepath</li>
  <ul>
   <li>Read <i>FilePath</i> and insert into the database. The full content is saved as a type blob.</li>
  </ul>

  <li>Delete any commit</li>
  <ul>
   <li>Select any commit to delete that commit. A vacuum operation will occur to reduce the size of the database.</li>
  </ul>

  <li>Edit the database</li>
  <ul>
   <li>Edit the database with an installed DB Browser for SQLite.</li>
  </ul>

  <li>Open any commit</li>
  <ul>
   <li>Select any commit to open a new tab and insert the content into the editor pane.</li>
  </ul>

  <li>Print all comments</li>
  <ul>
   <li>Print all comments from the database to the output pane.</li>
  </ul>

  <li>Restore any commit to edit pane</li>
  <ul>
   <li>Select any commit to clear the content and then insert the content from the commit into the editor pane.</li>
  </ul>

  <li>Restore any commit to filepath</li>
  <ul>
   <li>Select any commit to write the content to <i>FilePath</i>.</li>
  </ul>

  <li>WinMerge any commit</li>
  <ul>
   <li>Select any commit to write to a temporary file and compare with <i>FilePath</i> in WinMerge.</li>
  </ul>
 </ul>



 <h2 id="02">ClearAll</h2>

 <p>Clear all annotations and marks.</p>



 <h2 id="03">ClearAnnotations</h2>

 <p>Clear all annotations.</p>



 <h2 id="04">ClearBookmarks</h2>

 <p>Clear all bookmarks. Does same action as <i>Search -> Clear All Bookmarks</i>
 from the SciTE editor menu.</p>



 <h2 id="05">ClearErrormarks</h2>

 <p>Clear all error marks created by double click on red error lines in the
 output pane.</p>



 <h2 id="06">ClearOthermarks</h2>

 <p>Clear marks that custom programs may add. The user may not see them unless
 were added by a script.</p>



 <h2 id="07">CopyFileDir</h2>

 <p>Copy file directory path to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="08">CopyFileName</h2>

 <p>Copy filename without extension to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="09">CopyFileNameExt</h2>

 <p>Copy filename with extension to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="10">CopyFilePath</h2>

 <p>Copy absolute file path to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="11">CurSelCountBraces</h2>

 <p>Count braces in current selection. Prints the result to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Braces:</p>

 <ul>
  <li>( )</li>
  <li>{ }</li>
  <li>[ ]</li>
  <li>&lt; &gt;</li>
 </ul>



 <h2 id="12">DiffFileNameExt</h2>

 <p>Diff <i>FileNameExt</i> with fossil or git.</p>



 <h2 id="13">EskilFilePath</h2>

 <p>Run Eskil to diff <i>FilePath</i> with a checkout</p>

 <p>Eskil expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"$(SciTEDefaultHome)\eskil\eskil.exe"</code></p>



 <h2 id="14">FrhedFilePath</h2>

 <p>Run Frhed to hex edit <i>FilePath</i>.</p>

 <p>Frhed expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"$(SciTEDefaultHome)\frhed\frhed.exe"</code></p>



 <h2 id="15">InsertDate</h2>

 <p>Insert date at position of caret. If <code>yyyy-mm-dd</code> pattern with
 digits is selected, the selection will be replaced with current date.</p>



 <h2 id="16">OpenAbbrevFile</h2>

 <p>Open a <i>abbrev.properties</i> file which are searched in the subfolders of
 <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="17">OpenApiFile</h2>

 <p>Open a api file which are searched in <code>"$(SciteDefaultHome)\api"</code>.</p>



 <h2 id="18">OpenChmFile</h2>

 <p>Open a chm file which are searched in the subfolders of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.
 Some other locations may be searched, example <i>scite.chm</i> in the root of
 <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="19">OpenFileDir</h2>

 <p>Open file directory in a file browser like explorer.</p>



 <h2 id="20">OpenHtaFile</h2>

 <p>Open a hta file which are searched in the subfolders of
 <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="21">OpenLuaExtensionFile</h2>

 <p>Open a lua extension file which are searched as <i>extension.lua</i>
 in the subfolders of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="22">OpenSciteVarsFile</h2>

 <p>Open <i>scitevars.cfg</i> file which can be used by PrintSciteVars.</p>



 <h2 id="23">PrintApiKeywords</h2>

 <p>Print keywords from api files, like those used in autocomplete.</p>



 <h2 id="24">PrintApiLuaPropFiles</h2>

 <p>Print api, lua and properties files.</p>



 <h2 id="25">PrintAsciiTable</h2>

 <p>Prints ASCII table to output. Includes Extended ASCII. May need
 to have the codepage set to 0 to show the Extended ASCII correct.</p>



 <h2 id="26">PrintCommentLines</h2>

 <p>Get comment lines from the editor pane and print to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Filetypes supported:</p>

 <ul>
  <li>au3</li>
  <li>cmd</li>
  <li>lua</li>
  <li>pas</li>
  <li>php</li>
  <li>properties</li>
  <li>ps1</li>
  <li>py</li>
 </ul>


 <h2 id="27">PrintCommentedCodeLines</h2>

 <p>Get comment code lines from the editor pane and print to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Same filetypes supported as PrintCommentLines.</p>



 <h2 id="28">PrintFindText</h2>

 <p>Based on <code>http://lua-users.org/wiki/SciteMiscScripts</code></p>

 <p>Like the find and search built into SciTE, except this can print the
 results to the output pane.</p>



 <h2 id="29">PrintGlobalNames... PrintGlobalTables...</h2>

 <p>Print Lua names and tables. Used for viewing and debugging the Lua
 internals which is why it is included as a extended tool for use as it
 is for special use.</p>



 <h2 id="30">PrintReminders</h2>

 <p>Find reminder lines in the edit pane and print them.
 Code concept from RSciTE.</p>

 <p>Currently searches for these words with a trailing colon:</p>

 <ul>
  <li><code>debug:</code></li>
  <li><code>reminder:</code></li>
  <li><code>test:</code></li>
  <li><code>testing:</code></li>
  <li><code>todo:</code></li>
 </ul>



 <h2 id="31">PrintSciteVars</h2>

 <p>Print SciTE property variables. By default, prints the standard
 variables defined in <i>SciTEDoc.html</i>. If <i>scitevars.cfg</i> is located
 in <i>SciTEDefaultHome</i>, the file will be read for property variable names
 and will include them. Comment lines starting with <code>;</code> or
 <code>#</code> will be ignored when the file is read.</p>



 <h2 id="32">ReplaceSelEscape</h2>

 <p>Escapes special characters.
 Currently does api, bat, cmd, hta, html, lua, py, pyw, sql.</p>

 <p>Escaping in general is very broad, though an example is for html:</p>

 <code><pre>&amp;</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>&amp;amp;</pre></code>



 <h2 id="33">ReplaceSelSortLines</h2>

 <p>Sorts a selection of text by line.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>item3
item1
item2</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>item1
item2
item3</pre></code>



 <h2 id="34">ReplaceSelSortList</h2>

 <p>Sorts a JSON style list.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>["item3", "item1", "item2"]</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1", "item2", "item3"]</pre></code>



 <h2 id="35">ReplaceSelWrapList</h2>

 <p>Wraps a JSON style list.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1", "item2", "item3"]</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1",
 "item2",
 "item3"]</pre></code>



 <h2 id="36">SelectCalltipColour</h2>

 <p>Change colours of both autocomplete and calltip popups.</p>



 <h2 id="37">StartExeFile</h2>

 <p>Executables can be added to subfolders, such as Frhed, for reading the
 <i>FilePath</i>. StartExeFile will instead run these executables without
 any arguments.</p>



 <h2 id="38">StripTrailingSpaces</h2>

 <p>SciTE can be set to strip whitespace characters at end of lines on save.
 This tool allows the user to strip the end of lines in the edit pane.
 Can be useful if the property of <i>strip.trailing.spaces</i> is not used
 globally or by the current filepattern.</p>



 <h2 id="39">ToggleCodePage</h2>

 <p>Toggle between 0 (ANSI), 65001 (UTF8) and the actual codepage.</p>



 <h2 id="40">ToggleDimComments</h2>

 <p>Toggle comment colours from normal colour to a lighter colour.
 Dimming may not be useful for general programming though debugging
 code with dimmed comments may help with focus. Toggles on or off.</p>



 <h2 id="41">ToggleExtendedTools</h2>

 <p>Initially, some tools may be not shown in the ListBox, due to not being
 suitable for regular use. This option allows the user to toggle the list by
 reshowing the ListBox with the changes.</p>



 <h2 id="42">ToggleHighlightCurrentWord</h2>

 <p>Toggle highlight current word at position of caret.
 For distraction free programming, default to off.
 Toggles on or off.</p>



 <h2 id="43">ToggleMonospaceFont</h2>

 <p>Toggle with monospace font and proportional font. If <i>font.override</i>
 property has been appended to global font properties, default font is
 monospace. This function allows proportional font.</p>



 <h2 id="44">WinMergeFilePath</h2>

 <p>Passes <i>FilePath</i> as 1st argument to WinMerge. As a consequence,
 WinMerge will show the <i>Select Files or Folders dialog</i>. Choose your
 settings and then press the <i>Compare</i> button.</p>

 <p>WinMerge expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"%ProgramFiles%\WinMerge\WinMergeU.exe"</code></p>



 <h2 id="45">WinMergeFilePath unsaved</h2>

 <p>Passes <i>FilePath</i> as 1st argument to WinMerge. The SciTE edit
 pane is read and saved to a temporary file, and that file is passed as
 the 2nd argument to WinMerge.</p>

 <p>This can be useful if you do not know the difference, especially if
 a messagebox asks to reload shows to determine whether to save or not
 after the reload. If the later is the case, select <i>No</i> to the
 messagebox and then use this tool to compare. <i>File -> Revert</i>
 can be used if <i>FilePath</i> on disk is wanted after the compare
 is done.</p>

